{
  "_comment": [
    "Authoritative glossary of tokens that MUST NOT be translated across any locale.",
    "Extracted from the ACRONYMS set in .orchestration/logs/e16-translate.mjs (t2 i18n-1).",
    "",
    "LOCKED STRINGS (do NOT overwrite in any locale re-pass):",
    "  - networkDiscovery.title in es-ES.json MUST remain \"Descubrimiento de Red\"",
    "  - networkDiscovery.title in fr-FR.json MUST remain \"Découverte du Réseau\"",
    "  - networkDiscovery.title in pt-PT.json MUST remain \"Deteção de Rede\"",
    "These three values are the e22 fixup; tests/network/NetworkDiscovery.i18n.test.tsx asserts them.",
    "",
    "Format:",
    "  terms    — exact-match list of acronyms / brand names / proper nouns. Locale-independent:",
    "             a term is never translated in ANY locale.",
    "  patterns — regex patterns; a value matching any pattern counts as a legitimate non-translation.",
    "  cognates — PER-LOCALE. Words that are spelled identically in English and the target",
    "             language AND are the idiomatic term there, so an untranslated-looking value is",
    "             actually correct (de-DE \"Name\", \"Status\"; es-ES \"Error\", \"Total\").",
    "             Unlike `terms`, these ARE ordinary words — they are only legitimate in the",
    "             locales listed. Matched against the WHOLE normalised value, never token-wise,",
    "             so \"Status\" is legitimate de-DE but \"Status Filter\" (de: \"Statusfilter\")",
    "             still gets flagged.",
    "",
    "Residual-English detection (scripts/i18n-residual.mjs) flags `isAcronymMatch: true`",
    "when the English value is fully accounted for by this glossary — those hits are legitimate",
    "acronym preservation, not real translation misses.",
    "",
    "IMPORTANT — these lists feed a TRIAGE filter, not a verdict. Adding a wrong entry hides",
    "real rot from a human translator (a false negative); a missing entry only costs one ten",
    "second glance (a false positive). When unsure, LEAVE A WORD OUT. Only add a cognate that",
    "is unambiguously identical AND idiomatic in that locale; verbs and participles rendered as",
    "UI buttons are almost never cognates (de \"Delete\" -> \"Löschen\", not \"Delete\")."
  ],
